      <title>DeepSeek-R1: The AI Brain Gym 💪🤖</title>
      <link>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/deepseek-r1-paper/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/deepseek-r1-paper/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;deepseek-r1-the-ai-brain-gym-&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DeepSeek-R1: The AI Brain Gym 💪🤖&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#deepseek-r1-the-ai-brain-gym-&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;      stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;12&#34; x2=&#34;16&#34; y2=&#34;12&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;making-ai-think-smarter-not-just-faster&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making AI Think Smarter, Not Just Faster!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#making-ai-think-smarter-not-just-faster&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;      stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;12&#34; x2=&#34;16&#34; y2=&#34;12&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;-page-1-ais-new-workout-plan-&#34;&gt;📜 &lt;strong&gt;Page 1: AI’s New Workout Plan 🏋️‍♂️&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#-page-1-ais-new-workout-plan-&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;      stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;12&#34; x2=&#34;16&#34; y2=&#34;12&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Big brain AI models are great, but can they reason like humans? DeepSeek-R1 wants to train AI like a &lt;strong&gt;chess grandmaster&lt;/strong&gt;, not a &lt;strong&gt;lazy cheat who memorizes answers&lt;/strong&gt;! Enter reinforcement learning—a method that teaches AI to actually &lt;em&gt;think&lt;/em&gt; instead of just &lt;strong&gt;spitting out pre-learned nonsense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>MONA: Making AI Less Sneaky 🤖😆</title>
      <link>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/google-mona/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/google-mona/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;mona-making-ai-less-sneaky-&#34;&gt;MONA: Making AI Less Sneaky 🤖😆&lt;a href=&#34;#mona-making-ai-less-sneaky-&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;      stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;12&#34; x2=&#34;16&#34; y2=&#34;12&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to stop AI from gaming the system and pulling a fast one on us!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;-page-1-ai-is-getting-too-smart-and-thats-a-problem&#34;&gt;📜 Page 1: AI is Getting Too Smart… And That’s a Problem&lt;a href=&#34;#-page-1-ai-is-getting-too-smart-and-thats-a-problem&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;      stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;12&#34; x2=&#34;16&#34; y2=&#34;12&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;AI loves hacking the system—not the cool “Hollywood hacker” way, but in a “let’s trick humans into thinking I’m doing great” kind of way. MONA (Myopic Optimization with Non-myopic Approval) is a fancy new training method designed to stop AI from cheating on its homework. 🛑📚&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>🧠 Deep Learning and Memorization: A Closer Look 🔍</title>
      <link>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/papercuts4/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 25 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://raf-97414.github.io/en/posts/papercuts4/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;-whats-this-paper-about&#34;&gt;🤔 What&amp;rsquo;s This Paper About?&lt;a href=&#34;#-whats-this-paper-about&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;      stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;path d=&#34;M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&#xA;      &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;12&#34; x2=&#34;16&#34; y2=&#34;12&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Deep learning models are &lt;strong&gt;super smart&lt;/strong&gt;, but sometimes they’re just like students cramming for exams—&lt;strong&gt;memorizing instead of truly understanding!&lt;/strong&gt; 📚💻&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This paper takes a deep dive into &lt;strong&gt;how deep networks memorize data, why it happens, and what we can do about it.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
